OL,3,CMedics appeal denied over shortcomings
OL,4,Cin care for patient who died
OL,6,FAt the time, the prosecution argued
OL,7,Fthe pair failed to put Mr Irvine in
OL,8,Fthe recovery position, recognise he
OL,9,Fwas struggling to breathe, and provide
OL,10,Fadequate care during resuscitation.
OL,12,FThe prosecution described it as a
OL,13,F"sad, troubling case" and presiding
OL,14,FCommissioner Sir John Saunders said
OL,15,Fthat "there was no malice from the
OL,16,Fdefendants".
